tive excursion. Assuming typical platform carbonate accumulation rates, the records of the Maokou Formation suggest $\delta$13Ccarb values fell at ∼ 0.01‰/kyr suggesting a catastrophic origin (such as gas hydrate destabilisation) is unlikely, although a volcanic source is possible.},
