 of CO2 include dissociation of gas hydrates and oxidation of organic matter during extreme sea level regression, as well as volcanic emissions from Siberian Traps eruptions. Continental floral and faunal distributions are consistent with this interpretation, as are oceanic delta(13)C patterns and variations in shallow-water sediment lithologies.},
