C also revealed that biomarkers {\&}gt;C {\textless}sub{\textgreater}15{\textless}/sub{\textgreater} (especially steranes and hopanes) and ‘biological' chain length preferences for {\textless}italic{\textgreater}n{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} -alkanes are vanished at a vitrinite reflectance between 1.38 and 1.83{\%} {\textless}italic{\textgreater}R{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} {\textless}sub{\textgreater}O{\textless}/sub{\textgreater} . Our data highlight that ‘thermal taphonomy' effects have to be carefully considered in the interpretation of biomarkers in ancient rocks and, potentially, extraterrestrial materials. {\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
